PN,31602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1775574665
OL,3,CArtemis II on way back to Earth after
OL,4,Cbreaking deep space record
OL,6,FThey also became the first humans to
OL,7,Fsee the far-side of the moon with the
OL,8,Funaided eye during the mission as they
OL,9,Fpassed behind it during the lunar
OL,10,Fflyby.
OL,12,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,13,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,14,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,15,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,17,FThey then entered a period where the
OL,18,Fmoon eclipsed the sun before making
OL,19,Ftheir journey back to Earth, with
OL,20,FMercury, Venus, Mars and Saturn
OL,21,Fvisible during the darkness.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1775574665
OL,3,CArtemis II on way back to Earth after
OL,4,Cbreaking deep space record
OL,6,FThe crew, made up of Americans Reid
OL,7,FWiseman, Victor Glover and Christina
OL,8,FKoch, and Canadian Jeremy Hansen,
OL,9,Fspoke to US President Donald Trump
OL,10,Ffrom space about their flyby.
OL,12,FHansen described how the crew had been
OL,13,F"giddy" as they came within 4,067
OL,14,Fmiles (6,545km) of the moon.
OL,16,F"When we were on the far-side of the
OL,17,Fmoon and out of contact with planet
OL,18,FEarth, we all knew it. It was a
OL,19,Fmilestone, we saw Earth disappear, but
OL,20,Fwe were so busy with the science,"
OL,21,FHansen said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1775574665
OL,3,CArtemis II on way back to Earth after
OL,4,Cbreaking deep space record
OL,6,F"We have such faith in our vehicle
OL,7,Fintegrity and such faith in mission
OL,8,Fcontrol we were just at complete peace
OL,9,Fand doing our job."
OL,11,FHansen also described how different
OL,12,Fthe far-side of the moon looked when
OL,13,Fcompared to the view of it from Earth.
OL,15,F"The gravitational pull of the Earth
OL,16,Fhas had a profound effect on the near
OL,17,Fside of the moon, changing all those
OL,18,Fdark mares, those dark patches of the
OL,19,Fmoon you see from Earth," he said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1775574665
OL,3,CArtemis II on way back to Earth after
OL,4,Cbreaking deep space record
OL,6,F"It's very different on the far side.
OL,7,FWhile you see some small patches of
OL,8,Fthose mares and deep craters, it's
OL,9,Fvery much absent on that side, so
OL,10,Fthat's really neat."
OL,12,FNasa's Orion spacecraft began its
OL,13,Fjourney to the moon after launching on
OL,14,Fa space launch system rocket from the
OL,15,Fagency's Kennedy Space Center in
OL,16,FFlorida on April 1.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
