PN,31606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1775574665
OL,3,CArtemis II on way back to Earth after
OL,4,Cbreaking deep space record
OL,6,FTheir mission surpasses the record for
OL,7,Fthe farthest human spaceflight's,
OL,8,Fpreviously set by the Apollo 13 crew
OL,9,Fwhen they travelled 248,655 miles
OL,10,F(400,171km) in 1970.
OL,12,FArtemis II used the same manoeuvre
OL,13,Fthat Apollo 13 did after its infamous
OL,14,F"Houston, we've had a problem"
OL,15,Fincident, when an oxygen tank
OL,16,Fexplosion ended hope of a moon landing
OL,17,Fbecoming a fight for survival.
OL,19,FIt will take the crew four days to get
OL,20,Fback to Earth, with a splashdown in
OL,21,Fthe Pacific expected on Friday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
